cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.HC

The paper focuses on developing an efficient and reliable epileptic seizure prediction system using intracranial EEG data. The methods used include quantitative analysis, pre-processing, and cooperative multi-scale CNNs for automatic feature learning. These techniques are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the study involves analyzing brain behavior, which could fall under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The pre-processing method involves converting time-series data into an image-like format, which could be relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the study aims to develop a system that can alert patients of impending seizures, which could be relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category.
